TITLE: Russia's war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Ukrainian officials and satellite images point to evidence of mass graves outside the besieged city of Mariupol as Russian President Vladimir Putin claimed its "liberation." Follow here for live updates.

TITLE: Court-martial results in first conviction of general officer in Air Force history
SUMMARY: A US Air Force general officer was found guilty of abusive sexual contact in military court in Ohio on Saturday, marking the first-ever court-martial trial and conviction of a general officer in the history of the military branch, the Air Force said in a statement.

TITLE: Tyson Fury retains WBC heavyweight title after beating Dillian Whyte in front of 94,000 at Wembley
SUMMARY: Tyson Fury retained his WBC heavyweight title after beating Dillian Whyte by technical knockout in the sixth round in front of a raucous 94,000 fans at Wembley Stadium.

TITLE: Strong winds, dry air propel Tunnel Fire in Northern Arizona
SUMMARY: The Tunnel Fire, which has been burning across northern Arizona's Coconino County for nearly a week, has now charred more than 21,000 acres, according to the US Forest Service.

TITLE: California man charged after allegedly threatening Merriam-Webster over gender definitions
SUMMARY: A California man was arrested this week after he allegedly sent threatening online messages to the Merriam-Webster company over dictionary definitions containing references to gender identity, according to court documents.

TITLE: Zelensky says Blinken and Austin will visit Ukraine on Sunday
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky announced that US Secretary of State Antony Blinken and US Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin will visit Kyiv on Sunday.

TITLE: Opinion: The surprising solution to gun violence
SUMMARY: New insights from behavioral science suggest there's more to situations than root causes like poverty or segregation and help us see progress on the gun violence crisis is much more possible than we've thought, writes Jens Ludwig.

TITLE: Biden administration to renew Covid-19 funding push when Congress returns next week
SUMMARY: The Biden administration will renew its push with lawmakers to secure Covid-19 funding next week when Congress returns from recess, a White House official told CNN, following inaction from the Senate on a $10 billion funding package before the two-week Easter break.

TITLE: Texas National Guard soldier remains missing after helping rescue two migrants suspected of drug trafficking
SUMMARY: A Texas Army National Guard soldier who went missing Friday during a rescue mission along the border with Mexico has not yet been found, according to a release from the Texas Military Department (TMD).

TITLE: Twitter bans 'misleading' climate change ads
SUMMARY: Twitter is banning misleading advertisements that go against the scientific consensus of climate change, the company announced on Friday, which was Earth Day.

TITLE: Detroit Tigers slugger Miguel Cabrera joins MLB's vaunted 3,000-hit club
SUMMARY: Detroit Tigers slugger Miguel Cabrera entered the vaunted 3,000-hit club Saturday with an opposite field single in his first at-bat at home against the Colorado Rockies.

TITLE: Chiwetel Ejiofor and Naomie Harris on how 'Man Who Fell To Earth' hits home
SUMMARY: When it comes to the human experience, Chiwetel Ejiofor has found it best represented by an alien.

TITLE: Bayern Munich wins 10th consecutive Bundesliga title after beating Borussia Dortmund
SUMMARY: Bayern Munich clinched its 10th straight Bundesliga title after beating fierce rivals Borussia Dortmund 3-1 on Saturday.

TITLE: Europe agrees to sweeping new regulations for tech platforms
SUMMARY: European policymakers have reached agreement on a sweeping package of new regulations for tech platforms that could mean big changes in oversight for everything from social media algorithms to digital advertising — and with potential ramifications worldwide.

TITLE: 4-year-old dies after grandmother forces her to drink whiskey, police say
SUMMARY: A 4-year-old girl in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, has died after her grandmother forced her to drink whiskey, police say.

TITLE: Man dies after setting himself on fire at Supreme Court plaza
SUMMARY: A man who set himself on fire Friday on the plaza in front of the US Supreme Court in Washington, DC, has died, according to the Metropolitan Police Department.

TITLE: An Illinois man accidentally inhaled a drill bit during a dental procedure -- and it ended up in his lung
SUMMARY: One Illinois man has even more reason to be scared of going to the dentist.

TITLE: Taylor Swift celebrates Record Store Day with limited-edition vinyls
SUMMARY: Taylor Swift is this year's global ambassador for Record Store Day on Saturday -- and she's marking the occasion with a special limited release on vinyl.

TITLE: All-private SpaceX astronaut mission to return home from the ISS after week-long delay
SUMMARY: The first all-private mission to the International Space Station is slated to complete the final leg of its journey in the next few days, capping off what turned into a longer-than-expected journey after bad weather kept the passengers on the space station for several extra days.

TITLE: Wildlife photography can change the way we see our planet
SUMMARY: This week, watch Mars' potato-shaped moon during an eclipse, meet Tanzania's Lion Defenders, explore ocean worlds, meet a Swiftie bug, encounter stunning wildlife and more.

TITLE: New Ebola outbreak declared in DRC after single case confirmed
SUMMARY: Health authorities in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) declared a new Ebola outbreak on Friday, after a case was confirmed in the city of Mbandaka, in the northwestern Equateur Province, the World Health Organization (WHO) said in a statement Saturday.

TITLE: Videos show moments a driver lost control of a tractor-trailer that narrowly avoided hitting an Ohio school bus
SUMMARY: Dashcam video shows the terrifying moments when a truck driver near Cleveland, Ohio, lost control of his tractor-trailer and nearly crashed into a school bus loaded with students.

TITLE: Three popular recipes from Stanley Tucci's cookbook
SUMMARY: "There is some truth to the old adage 'Most of the world eats to live but Italians live to eat,'" Stanley Tucci has said.

TITLE: Livia's Tiramisu
SUMMARY: The sister of Gianni Scappin, coauthor of "The Tucci Cookbook," shared this tiramisu recipe. Make the dessert while you await season two of the CNN Original Series "Stanley Tucci: Searching for Italy," starting this spring.

TITLE: Venetian Salted Cod Pâté (Baccalà Mantecato)
SUMMARY: This baccalà appetizer, from "The Tucci Cookbook," is best served warm on garlic-rubbed toast or on grilled polenta. Make the recipe while you await season two of the CNN Original Series "Stanley Tucci: Searching for Italy," starting this spring.

TITLE: 'Washington Crossing the Delaware' that hung in the White House up for auction at Christie's in May
SUMMARY: The famous "Washington Crossing the Delaware" painting, which hung in the White House from the 1970s to 2014, is coming up for auction next month, when it is estimated to fetch about $20 million.

TITLE: McCarthy to lead GOP lawmakers, including Marjorie Taylor Greene, to southern border
SUMMARY: House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy is set to lead a group of fellow Republican lawmakers to the southern border in Texas on Monday, amid debate over the Biden administration's decision to end a Trump-era pandemic restriction on the US-Mexico border.

TITLE: Can red states regulate abortions performed outside their borders? A post-Roe landscape would test just that
SUMMARY: If the Supreme Court reverses its long-standing abortion precedent later this year and lets states ban abortions within their borders, it will unleash a new legal and legislative fight over how far anti-abortion lawmakers can reach to target conduct that happens outside their state lines.

TITLE: Marjorie Taylor Greene confronted over old social media posts advocating violence against Democrats in court testimony
SUMMARY: Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene of Georgia was confronted in court on Friday over past social media posts advocating violence against Democrats. At the hearing in Atlanta, to determine if Greene is constitutionally barred from running for reelection because of her alleged role in the January 6 insurrection, the congresswoman repeatedly said she couldn't remember past comments or interactions.

TITLE: New Hampshire couple found shot to death in wooded area
SUMMARY: The bodies of a New Hampshire couple were found shot to death in a wooded area in Concord, police say.
